g.text: Interfacing: The woman stands motionless. Just a heap of clothes and flashers now -- maybe if you search her?

Hand/Eye Coordination: Alright, here's how we do it: As soon as that gun isn't pointed at you again, you dash right, then immediately close the distance. Left hand grabs the barrel, right one breaks the wrist...
Hand/Eye Coordination: Fire off a shot over her head and use the moment of confusion to close the distance. Left hand grabs the barrel, right one breaks the wrist...
Kim Kitsuragi: "Huh?" The lieutenant studies the swaying firearm. "My god, I think you're right."
You: (Whisper.) "Kim, I'm almost certain there are no bullets in that gun."
The Pigs: "CONFINED QUARTERS, ASSAILANT COMING AT ME! SPLIT-SECOND DECISION, FIRE AT WILL!"
The Pigs: "Wh... what is this?" The old woman looks at the treacherous weapon. "This isn't police issue. Police weapons have bullets. This isn't real!"
Hand/Eye Coordination: No... no-no-no-no. THEY'RE REALLY NOT. The gun wasn't even loaded. No shots fired. You're fine.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Looks like a bad case." He gives the woman a compassionate look. "But the question is what to do with her right now."
The Pigs: "What...?" The woman looks at the weapon in disbelief, her eyes suddenly reddish with tears. She looks straight down the barrel... and squeezes the trigger.
The Pigs: CheckEquipped("neck_tie") and Variable["whirling.necktie_personified"] == true
Horrific Necktie: You weirdo. Get outta here before anyone sees you.
The Pigs: CheckEquipped("ledger_damaged") or CheckEquipped("ledger_oblivion") or CheckEquipped("ledger_of_failure_and_hatred")

Hand/Eye Coordination: Alright, here's the plan: You hurl the ledger in her face -- already darting right -- and *immediately* close the distance. Left hand grabs the barrel, right one breaks the wrist...

Hand/Eye Coordination: Alright, here's the plan: You fling the chaincutters in her face -- already darting right -- and *immediately* close the distance. Left hand grabs the barrel, right one breaks the wrist...
Half Light: Like when he had the hanged man in his sights? You're a dead man.
Jump to: [The Pigs: ""SUICIDE BY COP! SPLIT-SECOND DECIS..."]
Hand/Eye Coordination: She's frantic, confused, teetering under all that gear... There's an opening, if you just move fast enough... If not, the lieutenant's got her on his sights.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Phew..." The lieutenant exhales sharply. "For a moment there..."
Physical Instrument: Host Almighty, don't count on *that*! You saw the binoclard can't shoot for shit!
The Pigs: "No one ever cares anymore," her voice is growing fainter as she rocks back and forth, slowly. "Why would they cheat me like this..."

The Pigs: "Why would they cheat me like this?! I don't have *ANYONE*!" She slams her heavy boot in the ground. The impact travelling through the planks, sends your gun through the crack, into the black nothingness below.
Interfacing: That gun was the single greatest thing you had. This is an enormous loss.
You: "Yes. This is what happens when you listen to too many cop shows on the radio."
You: No, I know myself. I know I'm gonna fail.
Logic: She's in a stupor. There's no telling when she'll snap out of it. If ever.
Authority: That... was the most honourable thing anyone has ever done, Harry.
Hand/Eye Coordination: She's frantic, confused, teetering under all that gear... There's an opening, if you just move fast enough.
You: "No gun is worth this risk..." (Slowly back away.)
Kim Kitsuragi: "You're right," the lieutenant agrees. "Let's call her out on this."
You: Hold on, why does that make me nauseous?
Inland Empire: That knowledge comes from a very dark place.
Conceptualization: *This* limbed and headed machine of pain and undignified suffering is grinding to a halt. Tired of walking the desert, it doesn't want to feel or think anymore.
You: "I'm done with this gun." (Leave it behind forever.)
The Pigs: Her scratched skin is warm to the touch, but the person inside doesn't even know you're there.
The Pigs: "Nobody's ever around," the old woman mumbles, staring blank at the boardwalk, "nobody ever comes to visit me."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I guess I'll just notify my station. They'll contact the Sanitarium and handle the logistics."
You: She will *know*. (Hang the Setting Sun medal on her chest.)

The Pigs: "Mr. Morrand... Gareth, thank you. Thank you!" As the sharp end of the pin grazes the flesh, a blessed smile emerges. Then it expires, and like a shadow moving on the ground, all sentience fades again.
Inland Empire: No. A strange feeling fills your gut and suddenly you *know* the gun is empty. Thinking about it makes you nauseous.
Hand/Eye Coordination: Sure, you're you. But how do we end this? She's not just gonna let you leave.
Esprit de Corps: I was 80% sure the gun is empty and *still* the instinct almost took over.
Physical Instrument: Yeah, with shit-eyes it must be, binoclard.
You: "I'm very sorry this is how life turned out for you." (Gently touch her shoulder.)
Kim Kitsuragi: "I don't think she actually..." The lieutenant shakes his head. "You're right of course. This could've been very bad."
Esprit de Corps: Kim Kitsuragi is a nice guy. Wish he was here right now.
Inland Empire: In there she is alone, trapped in a world of blue and red lights.
You: "Wait, I was really hoping I can give her one of those station call slips..."
The Pigs: But it feels like *you* are, because the old woman standing there is motionless, emotionless and unresponsive. Almost like an inanimate object.
Esprit de Corps: Morrand's from Traffic.
Conceptualization: She must have built a new -- sadly better -- reality from the only material available: radio waves and cop shows.
The Pigs: A click. Nothing happens. She looks at the useless weapon. "This isn't police issue. Police weapons have bullets. This isn't real! What is this?"

Hand/Eye Coordination: Alright, this is how we do it: You hurl the tare bag in her face -- already darting right -- and *immediately* close the distance. Left hand grabs the barrel, right one breaks the wrist...
Inland Empire: No. An ominous feeling fills your gut and suddenly you *know* the gun is empty. Thinking about it makes you nauseous.
Logic: NO! Remember, 'Get the gun, it's okay. It's safe'? It must have meant the gun is not loaded. She's holding an empty gun.
You: "Go ahead, pull the trigger. I dare you."
Inland Empire: 'Paint the wall with your brains' dark.
Authority: That... was the most honourable thing *anyone* has ever done. You are virtue embodied.
You: "My god, it's not loaded... The gun isn't loaded!"
You: "Ma'am, the weapon you're holding is mine and I *know* it has no bullets."
Alright, what am I gonna do with you? (Proceed.)
Kim Kitsuragi: Weapon still trained on The Pigs, the lieutenant swiftly reaches down to snatch up the gun.
You: "I think we can just leave her like this. She'll be fine."
Kim Kitsuragi: "We could let Titus know. This is a perfect problem for the local 'peacekeepers' to handle. They might even know her family."
Interfacing: Grab the gun! Right now! This might be your *ONLY* chance.
Kim Kitsuragi: "God..." the lieutenant exhales loudly and uses his off-hand to wipe his forehead. "I almost blew her head off..."
The Pigs: The gun lands on the wooden planks and tears run down her scratched cheeks. "Police guns always have bullets... What is this? Why did you sell me this?"
You: "What do you think is happening to her?"
You: "You're not alone. We're all here."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Could be," agrees the lieutenant. "Her hands were trembling and she did seem uncoordinated... But what are we gonna do with her?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "There's a bit more to this than that," the lieutenant disagrees. "But right now we need to decide what to do with her."
You: "I don't want to endorse the Hardie boys' inflated sense of self-worth. They're not cops -- we are."
Authority: That... was the most honourable thing anyone has ever done.
Interfacing: She stands motionless. Just a heap of clothes and flashers now -- maybe if you search her once more?
HUB TO THEN END OF THE WORLD
Half Light: A madwoman is pointing a gun at a cop and you're thinking about warning shots?! Fuck the protocol! Shoot to kill.
Visual Calculus: No. That won't be necessary. Look closer. The gun, all three barrels, red and blue light shining through -- it's not loaded.
Inland Empire: That gun is a joke compared to the actual greatest thing he lost.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Poor woman..." The lieutenant holsters his pistol. "We need to figure out what to do with her now."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Probably not," the lieutenant agrees. "But more pressing is the question of what to do with her right now?"
Empathy: He's trying not to think about how bad it could have been had the gun been loaded.
Esprit de Corps: Lieutenant Kitsuragi would probably know what to do, but right now you're just gonna have to leave her like this.
You: "Cross me again and I will bury you, Pigs."
The Pigs: The catatonic woman doesn't understand -- probably even hear -- your kind words. She just *is*.
Authority: It's a shame. Recognition from an actual police officer would probably mean a lot to her. Too bad she'll never know...
Empathy: Exactly. With only the voice of Gareth Morrand to accompany her on Channel 8.
Logic: Her children and their children, if there were any, stopped coming when it got really bad.
Physical Instrument: It's all nancies up there in Traffic. I count zero balls.
Hand/Eye Coordination: Okay, you need to figure out what to do with her now.

Hand/Eye Coordination: Here's the plan: Drop the multitool and immediately dart right -- the noise will startle her, allowing you to close the distance. Left hand grabs the barrel, right one breaks the wrist...

Kim Kitsuragi: "She's in a stupor," the lieutenant replies, inspecting the catatonic woman standing in the dark. "I've seen this before. God knows for how long... Could be days when they get like this."
The Pigs: The catatonic woman -- especially now that she's unarmed -- doesn't seem to be a threat to anyone, but herself.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Then we can ask him once we get back to the Whirling. But we have to hurry, cause it's late and they might have already gone home."
The Pigs: Soon someone might have to. Doesn't look like there's much life left in her.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Okay," he nods. "That settles it. I'll contact my station after we wrap it up for the day. They can contact the Sanitarium and handle the logistics."
Composure: No. Wait... Earlier the lieutenant noticed something. Something about the gun... Could it be empty without her knowing it?
The Pigs: "SUICIDE BY COP! SPLIT-SECOND DECISION. EAT LEAD, SCUMBAG!"
Reaction Speed: In your peripheral vision the lieutenant releases the half-squeezed trigger.
Hand/Eye Coordination: Oh... I see. Okay, the gun was empty. All is good. You're fine.
Kim Kitsuragi: "I don't think there's any need for that. In her current state -- and without the gun -- she isn't really a threat to anyone."
Half Light: Take her to the farm. Put her down.
Kim Kitsuragi: "I've had... disturbances similar to this before. Many calls, but... never this bad."
Hand/Eye Coordination: Here's the plan: You jerk left, dash right, close the distance and cut her hand off. Ready?
Half Light: OH MY GOD, YES!!!!

Hand/Eye Coordination: Here's the plan: Shine the light straight in her eye and immediately dart right-- the light will blind her, allowing you to close the distance. Left hand grabs the barrel, right one breaks the wrist...

Hand/Eye Coordination: Porta-reel is the key. Up the volume to the *MAX* and hit 'Play'. The sound will startle her, allowing you to close the distance. Left hand grabs the barrel, right one breaks the wrist...
Kim Kitsuragi: "Situation is under control!" The lieutenant's voice rings over the police siren. "You're not shot, she's not a threat, everybody stay calm!"
The Pigs: The person who did that is no longer there. No one is right now. The empty shell of an old woman is slowly rocking back and forth.
Kim Kitsuragi: "No," the lieutenant sharply interjects. "That is not an option. We'll either unload this to Titus and his guys or I'll ask for help from my station."
You: Quietly leave the old woman alone.
You: "No, I'm *really* done with it. You keep it."
You: "Titus wants to be the sheriff, I'll tell him where to find you. Maybe he knows your family."
The Pigs: As you turn to leave, the faintest of voices comes from the woman. "Please, leave the radio on..." she mutters. It seems like a reflex, a half-remembered sentence.
Logic: Reflex to what? Being left alone?
You: Time to get my gun!
Physical Instrument: ...fingers lock behind her head, knee to the face, knee to the face, crush the ribcage, side-step and drop her with the hammer kick.
You: "But why was she like this in the first place?"
The Pigs: The woman stands in front of you, motionless, unresponsive. Almost like an inanimate object now. A mountain of police paraphernalia.
You: "Yeah, Titus sounds like the man for the job."
You: "At ease, patrol officer Pigs, your heart is in the right place." (Bow.)
The Pigs: Doesn't look like she would know the difference anyway.

Hand/Eye Coordination: Alright, this is how we do it: You fling the prybar at her-- already darting right -- and *immediately* close the distance. Left hand grabs the barrel, right one breaks the wrist...
Kim Kitsuragi: "I've been thinking that too. But it's impossible to tell for certain in these lighting conditions."
Pain Threshold: CONDITION BLACK, ALL SYSTEMS CRITICAL!
Kim Kitsuragi: "That would just be a waste of paper. I mean look at her." His eyes travel back to the old woman. "She's not going to respond to a station slip."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Okay but..." He bites his lip and mumbles under his breath: "... probably couldn't change your mind anyway... Let's go then."
The Pigs: As you turn to leave, the faintest of voices comes from the old lady. It's but a reflex -- nothing else. "Please leave the radio on... Mr. Morrand is on Channel 8..."
Hand/Eye Coordination: The gun, throw it in her face -- she won't see it coming. As she tries to catch or evade, you close the distance. Left hand grabs the barrel, right one breaks the wrist...
Kim Kitsuragi: "Oh, before we go..." The lieutenant pulls out your service pistol. "I believe this belongs to you."
Kim Kitsuragi: "But I think we're done here for now. Let's head out, this is done."

Shivers: A drop of sweat runs down your nose and in it you see the Martinaise inlet, wrapped in the night. In the abandoned fish market three figures stand in a spectacular light-show. A large, loud woman is pointing an empty firearm at the other two. She doesn't want to listen... or even to be heard.

Shivers: A drop of sweat runs down your nose and in it you see the Martinaise inlet, wrapped in the night. In the abandoned fish market two figures face each other in a spectacular light-show. One of them is forced to stare into the three empty barrels of a gun. Not an uncommon sight in the neighbourhood.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Honestly, I don't know. Dementia, probably," he lowers his voice. "Dementia and Channel 8. And loneliness."
You: "Thank you, Kim. I *do* actually want my gun back."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Of course. Understandably things got a bit hectic before. Don't worry about it." He smiles as he hands you the weapon. "Reunited at last. Let's go now."
You: Nah, that's not worth it.
Half Light: A madwoman is pointing a gun at two police officers and you're thinking about warning shots?! Fuck the protocol! Take her out!
Conceptualization: Great gears are grinding to a halt. The machine is powering down. She's all out of jolt.
Logic: The locals will take care of her. Someone's bound to know her family. Nothing you can do for her anymore.
Esprit de Corps: I was 95% sure the gun is empty and *still* that instinctual muscle twitch could have ended in an unnecessary death.
Encyclopedia: Mr. Morrand? Mr. Gareth Morrand, the former cop, turned Channel 8 crime show host? That Gareth Morrand from the radio?
Jump to: [The Pigs: ""CONFINED QUARTERS, ASSAILANT COMIN..."]
Interfacing: No! Look how she's holding it. Like it's light in the nose. It must be... That means the gun is empty!
